{
  "texts": [
    "Despite human participants having a broader range of unique responses, the fluency uniqueness did not appear to advantage semantic distance scores when comparing groups.",
    "The present study offers novel evidence on the current state of large language models (i.e., GPT-4) and the capabilities of divergent creative output in comparison to human participants.",
    "Overall, GPT-4 was more original and elaborate than humans on each of the divergent thinking tasks, even when controlling for fluency of responses.",
    "In other words, GPT-4 demonstrated higher creative potential across an entire battery of divergent thinking tasks (i.e., Alternative Uses Task, Consequences Task, and Divergent Associations Task).",
    "Notably, no other study has comprehensively assessed multiple dimensions of the most frequently used divergent thinking tasks and AI."
  ]
}